also one of the most well-known world events of the 20th century: The Ebola Epidemic. This year marked the anniversary of that infamous event. According to the BBC, 11,300 people died directly from Ebola in Sierra Leone, during the 2014–2015 outbreak. After watching the video below, 20-year-old Sierra Leonean bus conductor, Dish Warren, reflected:

“As a Sierra Leonean living in Freetown, I will take note of [the Ebola epidemic] to prevent this deadly disease, especially with the getting cross-over season. With LUMEN’s awareness, people will likely be more careful and aware of this disease and its symptoms.”

Dish and Leonard, who works at an elementary school as a day laborer in Freetown, plan to feature the LUMEN Eye Technique in their business: Warren & Co.’s Law and Taxation Services.

“A lot of people die from Ebola and thousands of people get infected. (…) I go to the market at least three times a week to sell food. I encourage all the market vendors to be conscious about this disease and use the LUMEN Eye technique.” – Warren

They all shared one common theme: through LUMEN, they hope they will be able to implement positive change in Sierra Leone, and in their everyday life.
